rComments: Awesome prof, definitely recommend, she has a great sense of humour and lectures are interesting
very sweet lady, attend class because she gives good examples to help understand the theory. mid term was a joke. final was tricky. assignments are easy just show up! Great prof

She's everything that a good prof should be. She's sweet, entertaining, and helpful. And for a course that is relatively boring she still made me want to listen and class. Doesnt post slides so you'll need to go to class. Make sure you attend at least the class before the exam and midterm because she gives out really good hints!

Prof. Leck was without a doubt the best prof. I have ever had! She really cares about her students and gives a very clear outline for what we will be tested on. She's always hilarious and very friendly. I wish she could teach all of my courses!! As for the course, ADM2336 is an easy A if you attend class and study!
Promotes gender inequality. Course is really an undergrad course taught at the MBA level. Tests focus on definitions instead of analysis and problem solving.

Love love love Professor Leck. Easily one of the best profs I've had at the university. Nice, interesting lectures, and very approachable. Midterms, finals and assignments were all easy/reasonable. Very fair overall.

Professor Leck is one of my favorite professors. She is very friendly and is always happy to help if you are having a bit of trouble. Her lessons are interesting, fun and easy to understand and the course is very well structured. I will definitely look into taking another of her courses :)
Friendly and knowledgeable prof. Keeps things interesting during lectures. And most importantly, her midterms and case studies were very reasonable; study and you will do fine.
She's helpful and amazing! Take her OB and HR if ur in Telfer!!!
Nice Prof I've ever had. Made u interested in the subject. She really knows her stuff. She's so kind and talks about her kids sometimes. She has two adopted Chinese daughters
She is amazing. The best prof I have had a uOttawa. Make sure you take a class with her. Her classes are very interactive, group oriented and she is so personable and fun.

Love her! Super fun and cute prof! Really easy marking for case studies and midterm was all questions from the discussion questions of the textbook with easy marking for that as well. Exam was a bit difficult thought (100 MC). Tip: use the summary notes on the organizational behaviour textbook website! super helpful.
Great Prof, very nice. Can get boring with all her videos but very helpful. I reccomend her
Knows her material, very effective in conveying subject matter, very considerate and understanding to students, friendly and has a great sense of humour, not oldfashioned at all! Great prof overall!
Great prof, is able to keep students interested and make the subject fun while maintaining control over the class at the same time.  Highly recommended!
She is a great person! Very helpful and fun. She knows her stuff! Take advantage of her. She will help you. However read the text front to back if you want to pass the course.
